@NODE INTRO "Introduction"

    @{b}Introduction:@{ub}

  Because all the libraries on the Amiga are released
  for the C/C++ langage format, Blitz 2 users need to
  convert some files before they can use the library.

  Hopefully, a program called FDConvert (and better,
  NewFDConvert) is used to convert automatically the
  library functions into tokenized Blitz 2 functions.

  Nevertheless, you don't have the include file,
  which contain all the strutures and constants
  used by the library. And you have to convert them.
  Manually. It's very boring and time consuming.

  At this moment, OpenBLitz enter the game. It will
  simply take your include file and convert it in
  Blitz 2 format. Only that :-). The result is near
  from perfect for about all includes files I've test
  (some bugs persist...). You must do the needed
  corrections by hands.

@ENDNODE


