@NODE INSTA "Installation"

    @{b}Installation:@{ub}

  Drag the file where you want.

  ASL.library is requiered.

@ENDNODE


@NODE HOWUS "How To Use It"

    @{b}How To Use It:@{ub}

  Launch the program, and a little window will ask you
  what you want to do. OpenBlitz can operate in two
  ways:

    + Convert a single file (self explanatory)

    + Convert a whole drawer:
  In this mode, all the files are converted, without any
  distinctions. Very usefull for large convert (ie:
  the Rom Kernal Manual includes files...:-)

  All the files are outputed in the 'Ram:T/' drawer. 

@ENDNODE


@NODE SPEED "Limitations"

    @{b}Limitations:@{ub}

  OpenBlitz has been written to convert header files, not standard
  C/C++ programs. So don't claim me that it doesn't convert Netscape
  Comunicator C++ source correctly into Blitz code..

  + 'Union' stuffs within structures aren't converted
  + Fixed string can be changed as the convertor doens't take
    care if the info is inside a string or outside.

@ENDNODE


